/F1 11 Tf 0 -46 Td ([ ] Write down the 3 tasks that eat the most time each week - AI is only worth it if it) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td (   removes real hours.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td ([ ] Check whether the tool ever sends your data to train someone else's model \(read the) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td (   privacy page, not the marketing page\).) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td ([ ] Confirm the tool has a UK/EU data option or a clear GDPR position before any customer) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td (   data goes near it.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td ([ ] Ask "what happens if it is wrong?" for each task - low-stakes tasks \(drafts, summaries\)) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td (   are safe first steps; anything customer-facing needs a human check.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td ([ ] Set a monthly budget cap before you start - most useful tools cost under GBP 30/month) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td (   per person.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td ([ ] Pick ONE tool and ONE task to start with. Trying five tools at once is how AI projects) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td (   stall.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td ([ ] Give it two real weeks before judging it - the first few days are always slower while) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td (   you learn the prompts that work.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td ([ ] Write down the prompts that worked well - a shared "prompt library" saves the whole team) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td (   relearning it.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td ([ ] Tell your team what it's for \(and what it isn't for\) - unclear AI policies cause more) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td (   problems than the tools themselves.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td ([ ] Review after 90 days: did it save the time you hoped? If not, stop paying for it - no) Tj
/F1 11 Tf 0 -18 Td (   shame in that.) Tj
